added.title: Pepo The Pumpkinman
added.description: A magic hat brings the Titans' pumpkinman to life, but they have to figure out how to keep Pepo from rotting.

added.title: 50% Chad
added.description: Having grown tired of their current villains, the Titans hold an audition for a new arch nemesis.

added.title: The Score
added.description: The Titans have a hard time dealing with their emotions when an evil composer changes the music in their show.

added.title: Thanksgetting
added.description: It's Thanksgiving but the Titans are sick of the normal traditions so they create their own.

added.title: Croissant
added.description: A giant cocoon mysteriously appears in the Titans' living room, and no one can find Beast Boy.

added.title: Black Friday
added.description: Starfire is visited by three ghosts and shown the true meaning of Black Friday.

added.title: Caramel Apples
added.description: Raven and Starfire clash after Starfire creates a bond with Raven's father, while Robin, Cyborg, and Beast Boy struggle to return to Earth's surface after falling into a deep cavern.

added.title: Vegetables
added.description: The Titans try vegetarianism, but learn that not everyone is cut out for that lifestyle.

added.title: Thanksgiving
added.description: When Raven's father Trigon shows up for Thanksgiving dinner, Robin's seating plan isn't the only thing that gets ruined.

added.title: Meatball Party
added.description: Raven eats a bad meatball that causes tentacles to spring from her teeth and devour the other Titans.

added.title: The Curse of Elmore
added.description: When Gumball's schoolfriend Leslie finds an old video tape, the creepy mystery of Elmore's ghostly past unfolds. Featuring spooky and hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Elmore's Most Wanted
added.description: Gumball's dad has been revealed as "Elmore's Most Wanted" - but when the Chief of Police tries to investigate, things do not go according to plan. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Mother's Day
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais need to find the perfect Mother's Day gift. Will it be a cute card, a thoughtful painting or something entirely different? Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: Ancestor Act
added.description: When Gumball's sister Anais researches the Watterson family tree, she uncovers a long history of nonsense. Featuring hilarious clips from the first six seasons of 'The Amazing World of Gumball'.

added.title: The Potato
added.description: When Darwin has lunch with Idaho, he decides to stop eating potatoes in solidarity with his brotato. However, he finds his obsession with his favourite food harder to kick than he ever imagined so Gumball decides to help his friend curb his carb cravings.

added.title: The Pizza
added.description: The Wattersons have had a bad day, but it turns out Larry has too and it's about to get worse . . . for everyone! The Wattersons complain about their day and order a pizza from Larry. When they call to complain about their late pizza it's the final straw for Larry and he quits all of his jobs. Elmore's fragile commercial structure collapses and the citizens revert to a more primitive apocalyptic state.

added.title: The Egg
added.description: To impress the mother of Anais' playdate, Nicole forces her family to get classy. Nicole arranges a playdate for Anais with the son of a classy lady she met at the supermarket. She hopes that socializing with the right sort of people will help her children climb Elmore's social ladder. The Wattersons try to impress, but ultimately cannot help revealing their true natures. The grown-ups become convinced they want nothing more to do with each other, just as Anais and her playdate discover how much they have in common.

added.title: The Recipe
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the secret behind Anton's immortality. Anton's little toasty body disintegrates during a swim class. When Gumball and Darwin see Anton the next day, as good as new, they set out to discover his secret. It turns out that his parents use a special formula to bake new Antons when necessary. So the kids test it out at home and end up baking a clone army whose leader - Ant-one - wants to destroy Anton and take over the world.

added.title: The Shell
added.description: Gumball inadvertently cracks open Penny's shell and discovers who she really is inside . . . While performing a school play, Gumball is so nervous about kissing Penny that he accidentally headbutts her and cracks open her shell. They discover that under Penny's shell is an emotional shape-shifting inner self. Penny's father is determined for Penny to keep it hidden but Gumball encourages her to show the world who, or what, she really is . . .

added.title: The Question
added.description: Gumball and Darwin seek the answer to the biggest question of all: what is the meaning of life? They need to understand the point of their lives, so resolve to seek advice from everyone in Elmore. They ask people, animals and even planets but their answer comes from an unexpected source.

added.title: The Saint
added.description: Gumball doesn't believe anyone could really be as nice as Alan and sets out to find his breaking point. Alan is so good-natured that Gumball feels compelled to make him lose his temper. Despite turning the whole school against him, destroying his relationship with Carmen and even selling his parents, Alan remains understanding and happy. Defeated, Gumball and Darwin decide to adopt Alan's positive attitude to see if they can be more like Alan.Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends but realize he might not be so imaginary after all.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are unwitting accomplices in a gas station robbery.

added.title: The Picnic
added.description: Gumball and Darwin barely survive a school picnic in the Forest of Doom

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Sour Candy Trials
added.description: Craig goes on a mind-bending journey as he tries to eat the most sour candy in the Creek!

added.title: Turning the Tables
added.description: Craig dines at the restaurant where his older brother works and orders up a plate of REVENGE... and lots of breadsticks.

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Craig and the Kid's Table
added.description: It's a Williams Family Thanksgiving, which means it's time to reunite The Kid's Table! But when Bernard accidentally destroys dessert, Craig uses the power of the Kids Table to help save his brother from certain grounding.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: The Cardboard Identity
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon a mysterious bunker made of cardboard beneath the Creek.

added.title: Ancients of the Creek
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP discover an ancient fort that belonged to the first kids in the Creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: The Takeout Mission
added.description: Kelsey leads her friends on the most important quest ever, picking up takeout for dinner.

added.title: Dinner at the Creek
added.description: Bernard is left in charge for the evening, so Craig sets out to find his own dinner at the creek.

added.title: Tooth Fairy Tech
added.description: In order to earn enough money to buy a house, the Bears work as tooth fairies.

added.title: High Baby Fashion
added.description: The Bears enter Panda into a fashion contest, but he's got some fierce competition when Madam Malin and Madeline show up!

added.title: Teddi Bear
added.description: In an endless junkyard the Bears meet Teddi, a sentient teddy bear.

added.title: A Gross Worm
added.description: The Bears help Unica return an endangered alien worm to its home.

added.title: A Real Crayon
added.description: The Bears find a mysterious crayon that has the power to make anything they draw become REAL.

added.title: Gwen Scary, Gwen Lost
added.description: When Chef discovers his spooky Halloween pranks have never scared the kids he's devastated. Determined to get them this year, he agrees to hand over full control of his pranking to Gwen. Her plan turns out far spookier then Chef ever hoped.

added.title: Ghoul Spirit
added.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

added.title: Tu Ba or Not Tu Ba
added.description: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous Tuba Band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

added.title: Dude Where's Macaw
added.description: While trying to defend his elite gamer status Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

added.title: Gobble Head
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Falafel's Fun Day
added.description: When Falafel decides to pack up and leave the city, Apple and Onion have to convince him to stay or they'll have to leave too.

added.title: Apple's in Trouble
added.description: Apple is challenged to a fight by a grumpy Cheesesteak, so he and Onion go on a quest to find the source of Cheesesteak's grumpiness.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Apple's Focus
added.description: Apple decides to help Onion achieve his dream of competing on a baking show.

added.title: Lil Noodle
added.description: Apple and Onion must remain legit enough to be in their favorite rapper's music video.

added.title: Apple's in Charge
added.description: Apple is put in charge of the Dollar Store for the very first time.

added.title: Burger's Trampoline
added.description: After learning that Burger has a trampoline, Apple and Onion pay him a visit. Burger thinks they came especially to see him and is overjoyed.

added.title: Onionless
added.description: Onion needs to leave town so Apple has to survive the weekend alone while taking care of Onion's beloved plant.

added.title: Apple's Short
added.description: Apple wants to experience love.

added.title: Sausage and Sweetie Smash
added.description: Onion must stop Apple from falling prey to his obsession, but a certain phone game is proving to be quite an obstacle.

added.title: Selfish Shellfish
added.description: Apple and Onion are faced with a philosophical question: Are they truly doing good deeds for the good of other people or is it all just for them?

added.title: Apple's Formula
added.description: Apple needs to find a formula for comedy that will land him a movie role.

added.title: Appleoni
added.description: The wrong person is getting credit for a new dance craze.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Falafel's in trouble with the law despite pleading his innocence. Apple and Onion vow to break him out.

added.title: Say Uncle
added.description: A long lost relative of Steven's comes to town to aid him in unlocking the power of his mother's Gem!

added.title: Story for Steven
added.description: Greg tells Steven the full story of how he met Rose-Quartz.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Love Letters
added.description: Steven and Connie help Jamie the mailman with love.

added.title: Reformed
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Garnet chase after a monster that's been loose in the Temple.

added.title: Sworn to the Sword
added.description: Connie trains with Pearl to be a swordfighter.

added.title: Rising Tides, Crashing Skies
added.description: Ronaldo does some investigative reporting on whether Steven and the Crystal Gems are safe for Beach City.

added.title: Keeping It Together
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems revisit the Kindergarten and find a dark secret.

added.title: We Need to Talk
added.description: Greg tells Steven and Connie the story of how he learned about Gem fusion.

added.title: Chille Tid
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems try to relax with a slumber party.

added.title: Cry for Help
added.description: Steven's favorite TV show gets interrupted by a magical disturbance.

added.title: Keystone Motel
added.description: Steven, Greg and Garnet go on a road trip.

added.title: Onion Friend
added.description: Steven and Amethyst visit the strange world of Onion's house.

added.title: Historical Friction
added.description: Steven and Jamie put on a play about the founding of Beach City.

added.title: Friend Ship
added.description: The Crystal Gems explore an ancient Gem spaceship.

added.title: Little Homeschool
added.description: Welcome to Little Homeschool, a place on earth where Gems from all over the universe can come learn how to live together peacefully! But there's one Gem who refuses to attend.

added.title: Guidance
added.description: Amethyst has been helping Little Homeschool Gems find jobs on the boardwalk, but Steven isn't sure about her approach.

added.title: Rose Buds
added.description: Steven gets a surprise visit from some old friends, and an even more surprising introduction to some new ones.

added.title: Volleyball
added.description: Steven is determined to help Pink Diamond's original Pearl heal the scar on her face.

added.title: Bluebird
added.description: Steven questions the motives of a mysterious fusion that suddenly shows up at his house.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: All Wet
added.description: No one believes Ben when he insists that one of the other patrons waiting in line at the World of Wet Water Park is the nefarious Frightwig disguised as a common girl. So Ben must prove his case while protecting park goers from her master plan: to destroy the park with its own water pressure!

added.title: Villain Time
added.description: Ben must go alien to save the Hoover Dam from disaster, but when tough guy hero Tim Buktu swoops in to help, Ben must figure out if Tim is friend or foe.

added.title: Drive You Crazy
added.description: After the Rust Bucket breaks down at a Mobile Home Park, Ben discovers they've stumbled on to the last leg of the Cali 10 Hundred, an epic, off-road auto race where mad driver Le Grange has returned for revenge against those that disqualified him years ago.

added.title: Tomorrow Today
added.description: When Max drags the kids to see a defunct "House of the Future" built by his childhood idol, Ben discovers Steam Smythe is busy excavating the joint on the search for a powerful device that will allow him to create devastating weapons for his war on progress. Only Max's devotion to his childhood idol and Ben's faith in dreams can save tomorrow... today!

added.title: Story, Bored
added.description: During a book signing at a medieval castle, Ben must stop Hex from getting his hands on a grimoire that can fuse its user with mythical beasts, creating monstrous hybrids!

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: The Return
added.description: Ghostfreak has returned! And he has brought a Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein like aliens with him to help him shroud the Earth in darkness.

added.title: Be Afraid of the Dark
added.description: Ben travels into space to thwart Ghostfreak's diabolical plans. But is he hero enough to take on the Mummy, Werewolf and Frankenstein?

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ghostfreaked Out
added.description: Ben's internal demons get externalized when Ghostfreak escapes from his watch and becomes a full fledged being on his own. The renegade alien then realizes he needs to meld with Ben's DNA in order to survive.

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: End of an Era
added.description: The Time War races towards its dramatic conclusion, with the fate of the entire universe and everything in it since the very beginning of time resting in the hands of the Ben 10.

added.title: A New Dawn
added.description: The Time War brings Ben, Rook, and George Washington together to battle an alien conqueror.

added.title: Crowbar Jones: Origins
added.description: Grizz pitches his Crowbar Jones prequel film to Nom Nom, hoping Nom Nom will agree to appear in the movie.

added.title: Hot Sauce
added.description: A quest for their favorite hot sauce causes the Bears to get involved with a sting operation.

added.title: Mom App
added.description: Hoping to finally get the mom-experience, the Bears use an app that'll bring a mom right to their door.

added.title: The Limo
added.description: To help distract Panda from his girl problems, Grizz and Ice Bear treat him to a ride in a limo.

added.title: More Everyone's Tube
added.description: Through another video browsing session online, we get more videos uploaded by the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Rescue Ranger
added.description: Tabes helps the Bears rescue Charlie after he gets captured by a villainous game hunter.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: Pizza Band
added.description: The Bears get pizza at Papa Bear's Pizza Cave and wind up replacing the place's animatronic band. They're such a hit that they go on tour!

added.title: Adopted
added.description: The Baby Bears get adopted by an eccentric millionaire and get to live in his mansion.

added.title: Wingmen
added.description: In order to get some sleep, the Bears help an annoying bird find a new mate.

added.title: Braces
added.description: When the Bears go to the dentist, Panda gets braces. But, Panda finds out his braces grant him super abilities and the power goes to his head.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: The Mall
added.description: The Bears go the mall and encounter their human counterparts.

added.title: Insect Inside/Powerpuff Bluff
added.description: Insect Inside: Vile villain Roach Coach has a plan to infest Townsville with an army of cockroaches! The girls overcome their squirms to squash Roach Coach's scheme and force him to bug off./Powerpuff Bluff: Three local hoods get new identities when they find grown-up-sized Powerpuff costumes inside Townsville Jail. They terrorize Townsville while the Mayor mistakenly sends the real girls to the slammer.

added.title: Octi Evil/Geshundfight
added.description: Octi Evil: The heinous Him toys with Bubbles' mind by speaking to her through Octi, her favorite stuffed animal. Following Him's orders, Bubbles picks a fight with her sisters that lands them all in a time-out./Geshundfight: The Amoeba Boys' ill-conceived plan to stand in Townsville Park all night in the rain leaves them with a nasty virus that's really something to sneeze at.

added.title: Major Competition/Mr. Mojo's Rising
added.description: Major Competition: There's a new man in town, Major Man, a perfect superhero, who cuts in on the girls' turf. But the girls prove that even though they're minors, they're still the major part of saving the day./Mr. Mojo's Rising: Mojo kidnaps the Professor and forces him to give him the same superpowers at the girls. But once empowered, the true evolution of this supervillain chimp comes to light.

added.title: Stuck Up, Up and Away/Schoolhouse Rocked
added.description: Stuck Up, Up and Away: Bratty little Princess comes to town and wants to be a Powerpuff Girl. When she doesn't get what she wants, the girls will have to pay./Schoolhouse Rocked: The Gangreen Gang goes back to school at Pokey Oaks Kindergarten and become the school bullies. Since the girls can't fight in school, how can they stop them?

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Just Another Manic Mojo/Mime for a Change
added.description: Just Another Manic Mojo: The Powerpuff Girls lose their baseball in Mojo's house, offering him the perfect opportunity to destroy these pesky superheroines if he can only get them to sit still./Mime for a Change: An accidental bleach spill turns Rainbow the Clown into the malevolent Mr. Mime. He proceeds to turn Townsville black and white and dead all over.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: Buttercrush/Fuzzy Logic
added.description: Buttercrush: Buttercup falls for Ace, the leader of the Gangreen Gang. But when the gang exploits her infatuation to lure Blossom and Bubbles into danger, Buttercup shows them the real meaning of the word crush./Fuzzy Logic: Beastly bumpkin Fuzzy Lumkins goes wild in Townsville and only the Powerpuff Girls, with some help from a flying squirrel, can teach him to respect other people's property.

added.title: Boogie Frights/Abracadaver
added.description: Boogie Frights: The Boogie Man creates perpetual night by launching a huge disco ball to block out the sun. While evil creatures are dancing and destroying in the dark, the Powerpuff Girls plot to crash the ball./Abracadaver: Al Lusion, the old-time Townsville magician, pulls off his greatest stunt yet when he comes back from the dead as the zombie Abracadaver to haunt Townsville.

added.title: Telephonies/Tough Love
added.description: Telephonies: The Gangreen Gang gets hold of the Powerpuff Girls' Hotline and makes crank calls sending the Powerpuff Girls on a wild goose chases all over town./Tough Love: Everyone in Townsville loves the Powerpuff Girls! But the citizens have a sudden change of heart when Him sends out an evil gas turning the entire town against their favorite superheroes.

added.title: Bubblevicious/The Bare Facts
added.description: Bubblevicious: Bubbles is tired of people dismissing her as more sugar than spice. When she sets out to prove she's hardcore, she takes everyone by surprise, even Mojo Jojo./The Bare Facts: After Mojo kidnaps and blindfolds him, the Mayor has to rely on the girls' very different individual accounts of the crime to figure out exactly what happened.

added.title: The Rowdy Ruff Boys
added.description: Mojo Jojo creates the ultimate weapons against the Powerpuff Girls, boy equivalents! Enter Butch, Boomer and Brick, The Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Paste Makes Waste/Ice Sore
added.description: Paste Makes Waste: When Buttercup's taunting turns paste-eating classmate Elmer Sglue into a destructive Paste Monster, she gets out of a sticky situation by doing something against her tough nature, apologizing./Ice Sore: During a heat wave, Blossom discovers that she has a new power: ice breath. But when she doesn't use her new gift wisely, she gets a chilly reception from her sisters.

added.title: Uh, Oh, Dynamo
added.description: Worried about his little girls' safety, the Professor creates Powerpuff Dynamo, a state-of-the-art protection system, to help them in battle.

added.title: Cat Man Do/Impeach Fuzz
added.description: Cat Man Do: Bubbles saves a seemingly innocent kitty from the clutches of an evil villain. But when the girls discover it's actually the Cat who is evil, they must save the Professor from being the next victim./Impeach Fuzz: When Fuzzy Lumkins throws his hat into the mayoral ring and claims a surprise victory, it's up to the Mayor and the girls to wrestle the office, and the Mayor's actual hat, back from him.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Checkin' Out!
added.description: A trip to the supermarket has bizarre consequences.

added.title: Drama Bomb
added.description: The school play goes off the rails when the drama teacher interferes.

added.title: Watch It!
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls are tasked with keeping a priceless gem safe from thieves.

added.title: Man Up 4: The Donnyest Game
added.description: With Man-Boy on the loose, Donny must be prepared for anything.

added.title: The Oct-Father
added.description: When Princess Morbucks steals Octi, Bubbles' reaction surprises everyone, even her sisters.

added.title: Sideline Dad
added.description: When the Girls start playing soccer, the Professor goes overboard.

added.title: Escape from Monster Island
added.description: After Bubbles wins two tickets to see the girls' favorite band Sensitive Thugz, Blossom and Buttercup vie for her plus one. But when the Mayor's plane crashes on Monster Island, the girls must put aside their differences to save the day!

added.title: Princess Buttercup
added.description: When Buttercup starts spending a lot of time with her new friends, a group of bad-girl skaters called The Derbytantes, it seems the Powerpuff Girls are down to two, which delights Princess Morbucks, who wants to fill the empty slot.

added.title: The Stayover
added.description: After going overboard on the candy, Blossom and Buttercup wake up with no memory of last night and no idea where Bubbles is! They must piece together the events of last night and find Bubbles before the Professor gets back!

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Horn, Sweet Horn
added.description: Bubbles convinces the Professor to test his new transmogrifying ray on her new friend Donny the Pony in an effort to help him become the unicorn he's always wanted to be. But when it turns Donny into a monster instead, she must stop him before he destroys Townsville!

added.title: Root Beer Guy
added.description: Root Beer Guy works a boring job during the day and tries to write mystery stories at night. But his life is about to change when he witnesses Finn and Jake kidnapping Princess Bubblegum!

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: Lunch Break
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to finish a ten-foot sub.

added.title: Every Meat Burritos
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and Fives want Every Meat Burritos from the Jimbros' Burritos drive-thru.

added.title: The Thanksgiving Special
added.description: The park guys need to get Thanksgiving dinner for their families to save Thanksgiving.

added.title: Rigby in the Sky with Burrito
added.description: Rigby wants to accomplish at least one thing he said he would accomplish before his High School reunion.

added.title: Take the Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to deliver a cake to Maellard's birthday party.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: Sandwich of Death
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to find a cure for the Death Sandwich before Benson dies.

added.title: Limousine Lunchtime
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to clean Maellard's limo before he gets back from vacation.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: Last Meal
added.description: Muscle Man wants to eat his favorite foods before going on a diet.

added.title: Steak Me Amadeus
added.description: Mordecai wants to ask Margaret to be his girlfriend.

added.title: Free Cake
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby throw Skips a surprise birthday party in order to get free cake.

added.title: Meat Your Maker
added.description: After Rigby causes the guys to get locked in a meat locker, he must get help from some hot dogs in order to get them out.

added.title: Grilled Cheese Deluxe
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby lie about being astronauts in order to cut in line at a restaurant.

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: Dare Day
added.description: With Jeff on vacation, Sumo and Clarence egg each other on in a series of increasingly absurd and extreme dares. But will one of them put a stop to this dare day, before it goes too far?

added.title: The Trade
added.description: After accidentally trading away Chad's favorite baseball card, Clarence has to trade it back! Determined to become an expert, Clarence transforms himself into a slick salesman, before facing the ultimate deal.

added.title: Chadsgiving
added.description: Clarence is excited for Thanksgiving Dinner with Chad's parents, but Chad is worried that their unusually laid back demeanor and bizarre customs will make him look irresponsible by association.

added.title: A Sumoful Mind
added.description: When Jeff realizes Sumo's new classes have been rubbing off on Sumo, he attempts to further foster this newfound intellectual Sumo! But will Clarence's lowbrow antics reverse Jeff's hard work?

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Pizza Hero
added.description: It's the end of the school year, and as is tradition at Aberdale Elementary, Papa Marianio is slated to dish out his famous pizza along with a spectacle of song and dance. As the kids wait in excitement, they share memories about times with Papa.

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Lost in the Supermarket
added.description: During a trip to the supermarket with his mom, Clarence discovers produce adventure and coupon intrigue in aisle five...and every other aisle.

added.title: Dinner Party
added.description: When Clarence's mom takes Clarence to a stuffy dinner party, Clarence embarks on a quest for fun wherever it can be found.

added.title: Neighborhood Grill
added.description: Clarence is so troubled by the sight of his teacher in a social setting outside of school, he can't stop himself from intruding on her doomed blind date.

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: Goldfish Follies
added.description: Clarence buys a goldfish, but when the goldfish bag breaks before he can get home, Clarence must keep his new friend out of harms way and get him back into water before it's too late.

added.title: The Big Petey Pizza Problem
added.description: Jeff has everything in place for his birthday at Papa Petey's Pins and Pies but Gilben is also having his party there, stealing Jeff's thunder. Jeff gets even more upset when the kids suggest they merge their parities for a double birthday. Can Jeff learn to roll with the punches and share his special day?

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: Lil' Mac
added.description: Mr. Gus' nephew terrorizes Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve.

added.title: Pizza Eve
added.description: Uncle Grandpa falls for Pizza Steve's "girlfriend" and ends up in serious danger.

added.title: Taco Comet
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang go undercover to taste the most sought after treat in the cosmos: the Taco Comet.

added.title: The Great Spaghetti Western
added.description: Mr. Gus repeatedly runs afoul of a crooked mayor while winning the hears of the townsfolk.

added.title: Watermelon Gag
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets a watermelon stuck in his mouth, he is unable to ask for help and people interpret it as a comedy routine. As Uncle Grandpa's popularity rises, his friendships and morale suffer.

added.title: Nacho Cheese
added.description: Pizza Steve's father comes to visit the gang and almost immediately gets on their nerves with his over the top antics. Pizza Steve must get rid of his dad, and prove to himself that he doesn't need to live in his father's shadow any longer.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Ate My Homework
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa shows up and mistakenly eats a kid's Egyptian diorama for school, he helps the kid bring an actual pyramid to class, but accidentally unleashes an evil mummy on the world.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Future Pizza
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa travels back through time with a warning that Pizza Steve will do something to offend him in the next five minutes, Pizza Steve begins to obsess over what he could possibly do to offend Uncle Grandpa.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: Greed causes Pizza Steve's latest business venture to backfire.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Diary
added.description: When his diary winds up in the hands of Mr. Gus, Pizza Steve goes to great lengths to get it back before Mr. Gus can read all of his deepest, darkest secrets.

added.title: Misfortune Cookie
added.description: After receiving an ominous fortune, Uncle Grandpa must snoop out whom among his friends is an enemy in disguise.

added.title: Wiener Club
added.description: Puppycorn is determined to become the Hot Dog King and joins an underground hot dog eating contest called Weiner Club. Rick warns "you are what you eat," but Puppycorn doesn't listen and eats so many hot dogs he becomes the new champion of Weiner Club. Unfortunately he also literally turns into a hot dog, that the other club members reveal they are going to eat! Unikitty and the gang now must attack with vegetables and defeat the hot dog-eating baddies in order to save the giant hot-dog-shaped Puppycorn and turn him back to normal.

added.title: Trapped in the Tower
added.description: During a fun fireworks show, Unikitty and Master Frown become trapped in the horn of the Unikitty Castle when she catches Master Frown messing with her fireworks. Unikitty takes this as an opportunity to figure out why Master Frown is always such a Cranky McCrabby Face all the time, if only Master Frown would let his emotional guard down! She tries all kinds of tactics, a song, a dance, even a firework with a face drawn on it named "Professor Pow Pow, licensed therapist" Getting nowhere, Unikitty ends up raging out and setting the tower and all the fireworks alight. In desperation to not burn alive, Master Frown tells Unikitty a story about a younger Master Frown who was gifted a special lollipop but after a freak chain of events, was broken right before his eyes. Unikitty cries her eyes out and puts out the fires and then reveals it was her plan all along to get Master Frown to talk about his feelings!

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: After being rudely interrupted by Bim Bom during her daily morning song, an angry Unikitty takes the advice of her friends and writes down her feelings into a letter with the intention of keeping the letter to herself, but then accidentally sends it off, complete with postage! The gang then goes on a wild chase through the Unikingdom mail delivery service to keep that rude letter from getting into the hands of Bim Bom, and ultimately hurting her feelings. Turns out, Unikitty's "rude" is everyone else's "nice" and the letter was full of compliments.

added.title: Scary Tales 2
added.description: It's Halloween again and the gang is desperately trying to tell the scariest story to a couple of trick or treaters. Each of the characters takes turns adding onto the last story, going through a haunted glove to a haunted action figure to haunted everything, and even a spooky song! None work in scaring the kids when suddenly a full scale alien invasion happens right before their eyes! Still, the trick or treaters are unimpressed until Richard takes the story stage and delivers a story no kid wants to hear- instead of candy, the trick or treaters would get granola bars! The kids, and Puppycorn, run away screaming.

added.title: Old Lady Bodyguard
added.description: After being "bought" at a charity auction, Hawkodile is forced to spend the day as Old Lady Edith's personal bodyguard.

added.title: Grown Up Stuff
added.description: Puppycorn doesn't want to grow up. To ease his woes, Unikitty spends the day teaching him all the fun things about being an adult.

added.title: Stop the Presses
added.description: Richard's newspapers aren't selling, so his friends pull out all the stops to put the printed word back on top.

added.title: Time Capsule
added.description: The gang puts their favorite items in a Time Capsule to send 100 years in the future, but they get stuck inside right before the door seals. Dr Fox tries to convince the gang to let her use their favorite items to escape the capsule, and each character tells a story about why their favorite item is their favorite, and why Dr Fox can't destroy it to escape. Finally it's revealed that Unikitty's favorite thing was friendship and she trapped everyone in the capsule on purpose, so the future could see their friendship! Unfortunately for the gang, even after they surrender their favorite items to escape, it doesn't work and they have to wait 100 years to finally leave the capsule.

added.title: Music Videos
added.description: Unikitty hosts a live music video countdown show for the kingdom, presenting the ecstatic audience with the top 4 music videos in the Unikingdom, featuring our favorite characters. Unikitty & Hawkodile team up for a death-metal picnic battle video, Dr Fox sings an 80s synth-pop jam about creating the perfect dance partner with science, Puppycorn sings a ridiculous nonsense song about his perfect day, and Richard unexpectedly closes the show out with the best song in the kingdom, a blistering hair-metal rock ballad with lots of solos and passionate dancing.

added.title: Brock Most Wanted
added.description: When Master Frown starts ruining parties to earn a promotion from his bosses, the Doom Lords, Brock accidentally gets blamed for the calamity. He helps Frown ruin more parties to clear his name and prove he's not the real party pooper, but before long Brock is the most notorious criminal in the kingdom, and the Doom Lords hire him as Master Party Pooper. Desperate to get his promotion and save his friend, Master Frown recruits Unikitty to ruin one last party, Brock's Doom Lord initiation ceremony.

added.title: Bedtime Stories
added.description: When Puppycorn can't fall asleep, Dr. Fox uses an invention to bring classic bedtime stories to life. But the gang's presence leads to some surprising twists in these popular tales.

added.title: Dunklecorn
added.description: A mysterious relative, Uncle Donklecorn, shows up unexpectedly, claiming to be family. Hawkodile thinks it's just Master Frown and Brock in a donkey costume, trying to ruin things as usual, but Unikitty and Puppycorn are convinced Donklecorn is an old family member. Hawk follows his bodyguard senses and tries to prove that Donklecorn is a fake, until finally the real Master Frown and Brock show up and ruin things, just as he suspected they would. He admits he was wrong about Uncle Donklecorn, but all is forgiven and the friends dance it out together.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Puppycorn is sick of Unikitty always helping him out and doesn't want to be the "little" brother anymore, so he uses some of Dr Fox's 'grow taffy' to grow literally bigger than Unikitty. Meanwhile, a black hole is on its way to destroy the planet. But when Puppycorn takes too much and continues growing, he starts accidentally destroying the kingdom. Unikitty takes grow taffy and grows big as well to help out, but when they're both the size of planets, Puppycorn proves he can take care of himself on his own by destroying the black hole and saving the kingdom.

added.title: Castles and Kitties
added.description: Score Creeper traps the gang in a fantasy role playing game where they must follow a complex set of rules to win their freedom.

added.title: Brain Trust
added.description: Dr. Fox accidentally transports the gang inside her brain, where they must control her movements to complete a dangerous experiment.

added.title: Garden of Evil
added.description: Poison Ivy takes control of Swamp Thing using his vegetative powers to overwhelm Gotham with dangerous plants.

added.title: All Aboard the Space Train
added.description: In a strange turn of events, the JLA enlist the help of Space Cabbie and Jonah Hex to stop the hijacking of an intergalactic space train.

added.title: Time Out
added.description: Batman must team up with Booster Gold when an inter-demoniacal alien creature starts eating up time literally.

added.title: The Fatal Fare
added.description: Space Cabbie inadvertently learns about a great threat to the Justice League when one of his passengers turns out to be Darkseid.

added.title: Phased and Confused
added.description: When members of the Justice League are affected by the Phantom Zone ray and become phantom-like, their only hope for freedom is to somehow get a message to Booster Gold.

added.title: Origin of Species
added.description: Origin of Species, Part 1: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago./Origin of Species, Part 2: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

added.title: Burger Run/Monkey See, Monkey Don't
added.description: Burger Run: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!/Monkey See, Monkey Don't: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

added.title: Bully for You/Trolling for Laughs
added.description: Bully for You: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids./Trolling for Laughs: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

added.title: Local Heroes/Pegatrix
added.description: Local Heroes: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan./Pegatrix: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

added.title: Frenemies/Strata's Fear
added.description: Frenemies: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO./Strata's Fear: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

added.title: Cowbar Jones: Origines
added.description: Pardo presenta la precuela de su película de Crowbar Jones a Nom Nom, con la esperanza de que acepte actuar en la película.

added.title: Salsa Picante
added.description: La búsqueda de su salsa picante favorita hace que los Osos se involucren en una operación de picadura.

added.title: Mama a la Orden
added.description: Con el deseo de tener la experiencia de una madre, los osos usan una aplicación que les traerá una madre a la puerta de sus casas.

added.title: La Limosna
added.description: Para ayudar a Panda a distraerse de sus problemas románticos, Pardo y Polar le regalan un paseo en limosina.

added.title: Mas del canal de todos
added.description: A través de otra sesión de navegación por Internet, vemos más videos subidos por los Osos y sus amigos.

added.title: El Benefactor
added.description: Los Osos ayudan a Chloe a presentar su proyecto de ciencias para un concurso escolar. Pero el rival de Chloe complica las cosas.

added.title: Los Rescatadores
added.description: Cuando un cazador malvado captura a Charlie, Tabes ayuda a los Osos a rescatarlo.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: En flashes retrospectivos al pasado lejano, vemos una aventura de Charlie en el desierto mexicano.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: Los Osos bebé se inscriben en un torneo de lucha libre mexicana.

added.title: La Banda Pizzera
added.description: Los Osos van a comer a la Cabaña de la Pizza de Papá Oso y terminan reemplazando la banda animatrónica del local. iSon tan exitosos que terminan saliendo de gira!

added.title: Inaccion de Gracias
added.description: Llegó el Día de Acción de Gracias y los Titanes, hartos de las tradiciones normales, inventan una propia.

added.title: El Club Salchicha
added.description: Perricornio está decidido a convertirse en el rey de los hot dogs y se une al Club Salchicha, una competencia clandestina de comer hot dogs.

added.title: Atrapados en la torre
added.description: Durante un divertido espectáculo de fuegos artificiales, Unikitty y Master Frown quedan atrapados en el cuerno del castillo luego de que ella lo sorprende tratando de arruinar sus fuegos artificiales.

added.title: Entrega especial
added.description: Después de ser interrumpida por Bim Bom durante su canción matutina, una furiosa Unikitty sigue el consejo de sus amigos y escribe sus sentimientos en una carta con la intención de quedársela, pero la envía accidentalmente. La banda sale en una salvaje persecución de los servicios postales del Unireino para evitar que la irrespetuosa carta llegue a Bim Bom y hiera sus sentimientos.

added.title: Cuentos de miedo 2
added.description: Es Halloween de nuevo y la banda trata de contar aterradoras historias a un grupo de niños que piden dulces.

added.title: Halloween En El Arroyo
added.description: Llegó Halloween al bosque, y Craig se embarca en una misión para recolectar la mayor cantidad de dulces como sea humanamente posible. Pero un espíritu aterrador del pasado del bosque amenaza su botín.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Antología Del Otoño
added.description: En un intento por terminar un proyecto escolar, Craig recuerda algunos de sus momentos otoñales favoritos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: A Comer
added.description: Craig ingresa en una competencia culinaria en el bosque, pero le preocupa que el nivel sea demasiado alto para él.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dulce Acido
added.description: Craig se embarca en un alucinante viaje mientras trata de comer la golosina más ácida del Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Del Otro Lado de la Mesa
added.description: Craig almuerza en el restaurante donde trabaja su hermano mayor y pide un plato de VENGANZA… y muchos palitos de pan.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Craig y la mesa de los ninos
added.description: Llegó el Día de Acción de Gracias de la familia Williams, iasí que es hora de reunir a la Mesa de los chicos! Pero cuando, por accidente, Bernard destruye el postre, Craig usa el poder de la Mesa de los chicos como ayuda para salvar a su hermano de un castigo asegurado.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Triquicornio
added.description: Un misterioso pariente, el tío Triquicornio, aparece inesperadamente asegurando ser de la familia. Halcondrilo cree que solo son Master Frown y Brock en un disfraz de burro tratando de arruinar las cosas, pero Unikitty y Perricornio están convencidos de que Triquicornio en un viejo miembro de la familia. Halcondrilo sigue sus instintos de guardaespaldas e intenta probar que Triquicornio es un impostor.

added.title: Dolores del crecimiento
added.description: Perricornio está cansado de que Unikitty siempre lo ayude y ya no quiere ser el hermano pequeño, así que usa un poco del dulce de crecimiento de la Dra. Fox para ser más grande que Unikitty.

added.title: Ancianos de arroyo
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP descubren una fortaleza antigua que les perteneció a los primeros niños del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pijamada en casa de JP
added.description: JP invita a sus amigos para una pijamada, pero resulta ser la misma noche que un gran juego con linternas en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Videos musicales
added.description: Unikitty conduce un programa de videos musicales, presentando a la eufórica audiencia los cuatro mejores videos musicales del Unireino protagonizados por nuestros personajes favoritos.

added.title: La identidad de carton
added.description: Craig y sus amigos se topan con un refugio subterráneo hecho de cartón debajo del bosque.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Contrabandistas de Azucar
added.description: Craig, Kelsey y JP se convierten en contrabandistas para llevarle dulces a niños necesitados.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El baile de los Infusionistas
added.description: Los Infusionistas organizan un baile e invitan a todos los habitantes del bosque. Craig cree que el único propósito del baile es hacerle una broma a él, mientras que Kelsey debe lidiar con un admirador indeseado.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Se busca Brock
added.description: Cuando Master Frown comienza a arruinar fiestas para ganar un ascenso de sus jefes, los Señores de la Muerte, Brock accidentalmente es culpado por las desgracias.

added.title: La casa de munecas embrujada
added.description: Craig y sus amigos descubren que los persigue una muñeca aterradora y su casa de muñecas embrujada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Capsula del tiempo
added.description: La banda pone sus objetos favoritos dentro de una capsula del tiempo para enviarlas 100 años al futuro, pero quedan atrapados dentro antes de que la puerta se cierre.

added.title: Pequena Escuela Madre
added.description: Bienvenidos a la Pequeña Escuela Madre, un lugar en la Tierra donde Gemas de todo el universo pueden aprender a vivir juntas pacíficamente. Pero hay una Gema que se rehúsa a asistir.

added.title: Consejos
added.description: Amatista ha estado ayudando a las Gemas de Pequeña Escuela Madre a encontrar trabajo, pero Steven no está seguro de su enfoque.

added.title: Capullos de Rosa
added.description: Steven recibe una visita sorpresa de algunos viejos amigos y una introducción aún más sorprendente a algunos nuevos.

added.title: Voleibol
added.description: Steven está decidido a ayudar a la Perla original de Diamante Rosa para sanar la cicatriz en su rostro.

added.title: Azulejo
added.description: Steven cuestiona los motivos de una misteriosa fusión que de repente se presenta en su casa.

added.title: Un Episodio Muy Especial
added.description: Cuarzo Arcoíris 2.0 prometió cuidar de Cebolla el mismo día que Heliolita programó una charla sobre la seguridad del hogar. ¿Es posible para Steven estar en dos lugares a la vez y ser dos fusiones al mismo tiempo?

added.title: Dia de Nevada
added.description: Steven y las Gemas de Cristal tienen la oportunidad de ponerse al día en un día nevado.

added.title: Porque tan triste?
added.description: Steven ha escuchado rumores de un par de Gemas que todavía están destruyendo mundos. Si él no puede detenerlas, tal vez Lapis sí.

added.title: Escape de la Cena Familiar
added.description: En el arroyo se disputa una enorme pelea con globos acuáticos, pero Craig está atrapado en la cena familiar, a menos que pueda escapar.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Pequena graduacion
added.description: Steven y las Gemas celebran la primera clase de graduados de la Escuela Madre.

added.title: Duo Espinoso
added.description: Después de dejar Pequeña Escuela Madre, Steven ha encontrado un nuevo pasatiempo: las plantas.

added.title: Manzana, Concentrate
added.description: Manzana ayuda a Cebollín a cumplir su sueño de competir en un programa de pastelería.

added.title: En Suenos
added.description: Los sueños de Steven comienzan a transmitirse en el televisor de su dormitorio.

added.title: Bismuto Casual
added.description: Perla invita a Bismuto a la pista de patinaje para darle una lección sobre cómo forjar relaciones humanas.

added.title: Fideito
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben seguir teniendo la onda suficiente para aparecer en el video musical de su rapero favorito.

added.title: Juntos por Siempre
added.description: Connie tiene una visión muy clara de su futuro, y Steven quiere asegurarse de ser parte de esa visión.

added.title: Duele Crecer
added.description: Steven va al médico por primera vez.

added.title: Sr. Universo
added.description: Greg lleva a Steven de viaje para encontrar los orígenes del nombre del Universo.

added.title: Manzana Mandona
added.description: Manzana queda a cargo de la Tienda de Dolar por primera vez.

added.title: El Trampolin de Hamburguesa
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben encontrar una manera de usar el trampolín de Hamburguesa sin que él se sienta usado.

added.title: Sin Cebollin
added.description: Manzana trata de sobrevivir un fin de semana solo mientras cuida la planta de Cebollín.

added.title: Manzana es Bajito
added.description: Manzana tiene que ser alto para poder enamorarse.

added.title: Mision para llevar
added.description: Kelsey guía a sus amigos en la misión más importante de la historia: buscar la comida para la cena.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Falafel en la Carcel
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben sacar a Falafel de la cárcel por un delito que no cometió.

added.title: Cena en el Arroyo
added.description: Bernard queda a cargo de sus hermanos durante la noche, así que Craig se va a buscar su propia cena en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: La Formula de Manzana
added.description: Manzana necesita encontrar una fórmula divertida que le permita conseguir un papel cómico en una película.

added.title: Manzallin
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín quieren llevarse el crédito de haber creado una nueva moda de baile.

added.title: Salchichas y Dulce Golpe
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben superar sus obsesiones por las salchichas y los videojuegos.

added.title: Ego - Egoista
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla tienen que demostrar que no son egoístas cuando hacen sus buenas acciones.

added.title: The Boss
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Rocky land an office job so that his dad, Mr. Robinson, will be proud of him. After a health scare the kids decide to reunite Mr Robinson with his son. Mr Robinson has always seen Rocky as a disappointment so when Gumball and Darwin help him land a corporate job at Chanax, he is thrilled. However the Chanax corporation is not quite what it seems. Can Gumball and Darwin rescue Rocky before he becomes a corporate drone for all eternity . . .

added.title: The Friend
added.description: Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who turns out to be all too real. Anais throws a party but no-one shows up as she has no friends or social skills. Gumball and Darwin help Anais make up an imaginary friend who, much to all their surprise, appears in front of them. Gumball and Darwin teach Anais and her new friend how to become friends, but soon realise that he might not be so imaginary after all...

added.title: The Ape
added.description: Ms Simian sets out to "befriend" Gumball in order to win a Favourite Teacher Award.

added.title: Furniture & Meat
added.description: Big money problems send Finn and Jake to Wildberry Kingdom.

added.title: Apple Wedding
added.description: You are cordially invited to the wedding of the year! But who will be united in matrimony?

added.title: Red Starved
added.description: Finn, Jake and Marceline are trapped in an underground cavern with no red in sight. If Marceline doesn't feed, she will turn into a vampiric beast and suck out all of Jake's blood! Finn heads off to explore the cave and find something red to satiate her until they can be rescued.

added.title: Thank You
added.description: The Snow Golem and his beseeching pup pay a visit to the Fire Kingdom.
